		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=36958"><span id=Scholar>Beemo</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>176 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Beemo&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Had a good upper dogs night in Velks the other day.&nbsp;&nbsp;I can not decide wich to wear for my back slot.  Spider Fur Cloak 10AC 4str dex sta 6sv cold or shimmering terror hide at 8AC 4str dex 50HP.  I am thinking since my STA in under 100 even with the spider fur (97 with cloak) to keep it until I get my sta well over 100 and then switch to shimmering for the HP.  I am also wearing Treant Fists so I think with Gem inlaid I can just get mu 100 STA by that switch.  I can't decide if its pride I feel wering Treant Fist or if its the donky ears coming out of my head for wasting all that time on the Gob alchemist hehe.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Quanko Crakkers<br>65 Grandmaster<br>(<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87045" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87045</a><br>Xegony</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Tue, Dec 4th 1:42 PM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=100748090921697&post=1&replyto=100749135127752"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class=sm href="/db/journal2.html?user=35651"><img src="/shared/user_journal.gif" border="0" height="12" width="17" /> User's Journal</a>   <a name=100749135127752></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=35651"><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a><b><span id=Guru><br>Guru</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>684 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.18]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Keyeluke&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I had this question arise a while back.&nbsp;&nbsp;It led me to establish my own little guideline for comparing items:<br><br>8 HP = 1 AC = 2 Stamina<br><br>By this rule, Terrorhide is clearly the way to go.  I wear one, and am very happy with it.<br><br>A note on this 'guideline.'  Since the purpose of increased AC is to reduce the melee damage you take (hit points subtracted from your health), there is obviously an equivalency between HP and AC.  In the end, it is the same if you have an extra N1 hp to offset the damage you take, or extra N2 AC to reduce the number of hitpoints in damage you take.  Trick is to find the number X such that X*N1 = N2.  As for Stamina - Stamina = hitpoints.  At level 60 I read that it is 1 Sta = 4 HP.  Easy to plug that into the equation when you figure out what X is.  For that I deferred to the monks who have been at this a lot longer than I have.  It seems that monks at high levels tend to favor either AC or HP.  The AC monks often talk about a 10:1 hp/ac ratio, and the HP monks go as low as 5:1.  If you tank or solo a lot you might bias towards AC.  If you find yourself getting hit more by spells than melee (pulling casters, AoE's during fights, etc), you might bias towards HP (and of course resists). I do some of both, so I opted for a middle ground.<br><br>As for the Sta issue - well - it's mainly an issue if your stamina bar runs out regularly.  My stamina is in the high 80s.  I swing an IFS - used to swing Jade Mace/Fist - and I cannot recall the last time I drained out the stamina bar (excluding raids to Kedge Keep - where I made sure to get a Sta buff).  If you're not having stamina issues, don't sweat it too hard.  If you're a pulling monk, go for the terrorhide for sure.<br><br>As for the treant fists - well - nothing sez you absolutely have to go with the 'best' item out there.  How many monks now refuse to wear the CCS because every monk on the game is in baby blue?  Do what makes you happy :)<br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=100748090921697&post=1&mid=100748090921697><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">1 Post [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class3">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
